org.jcvi.jillion.sam

Enum SamRecordFlag

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<SamRecordFlag>
      • org.jcvi.jillion.sam.SamRecordFlag
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<SamRecordFlag>

    public enum SamRecordFlag
extends Enum<SamRecordFlag>
    SamRecordFlags is an object representation of the SAM bit flags column for each record.
    Author:
    dkatzel

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • HAS_MATE_PAIR

        public static final SamRecordFlag HAS_MATE_PAIR
        Notes that the read multi-mapped and so will have multiple alignment records.

      • EACH_SEGMENT_PROPERLY_ALIGNED

        public static final SamRecordFlag EACH_SEGMENT_PROPERLY_ALIGNED

      • READ_UNMAPPED

        public static final SamRecordFlag READ_UNMAPPED
        This is the only reliable place to tell whether the read is unmapped. If READ_UNMAPPED is set, no assumptions can be made about SamRecord.getReferenceName(), SamRecord.getStartPosition(), SamRecord.getCigar(), SamRecord.getMappingQuality() and the SamRecordFlags : EACH_SEGMENT_PROPERLY_ALIGNED, REVERSE_COMPLEMENTED, SECONDARY_ALIGNMENT, SUPPLEMENTARY_ALIGNMENT and MATE_REVERSE_COMPLEMENTED of the previous read in the template.

      • MATE_UNMAPPED

        public static final SamRecordFlag MATE_UNMAPPED
        Does this read's mate have its READ_UNMAPPED flag set.

      • REVERSE_COMPLEMENTED

        public static final SamRecordFlag REVERSE_COMPLEMENTED
        Is this read reverse complemented. If this flag is present, then this read's Direction is Direction.REVERSE; otherwise it's Direction.FORWARD.

      • MATE_REVERSE_COMPLEMENTED

        public static final SamRecordFlag MATE_REVERSE_COMPLEMENTED
        Does this read's mate have its REVERSE_COMPLEMENTED flag set.

      • FIRST_MATE_OF_PAIR

        public static final SamRecordFlag FIRST_MATE_OF_PAIR

      • SECOND_MATE_OF_PAIR

        public static final SamRecordFlag SECOND_MATE_OF_PAIR
        This the second read of a mate pair.

      • SECONDARY_ALIGNMENT

        public static final SamRecordFlag SECONDARY_ALIGNMENT
        Marks the alignment not to be used in certain analyses when the tools in use are aware of this. It is typically used to flag alternative mappings when multiple mappings are presented in a SAM.

      • FAILED_QC

        public static final SamRecordFlag FAILED_QC
        This read has failed some kind of QC check.

      • DUPLICATE

        public static final SamRecordFlag DUPLICATE

      • SUPPLEMENTARY_ALIGNMENT

        public static final SamRecordFlag SUPPLEMENTARY_ALIGNMENT
        Indicates that the corresponding alignment line is part of a chimeric alignment. A line flagged with this is called as a supplementary line.

      • parseFlags

        public static Set<SamRecordFlag> parseFlags(int bitFlags)
        Parse the given bit flags (as an int) into the equivalent Set of SamRecordFlags. The input of this method should be the output of asBits(Set) and vice versa.
        Parameters:
        bitFlags - the bitFlag representation as an int; msut be >=0.
        Returns:
        a Set of SamRecordFlags; will never be null but may be empty if no flags are set (bitFlags ==0 ).
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if bitFlags is negative.
        See Also:
        asBits(Set)

      • asBits

        public static int asBits(Set<SamRecordFlag> flags)
        Compute the integer bit flag value of the given Set of SamRecordFlags. The input of this method should be the output of parseFlags(int) and vice versa.
        Parameters:
        flags - the flags to set; can not be null
        Returns:
        an int, will never be < 0.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if flags is null.
        See Also:
        SamRecordFlags#parseFlags(int)
